  "prompt": "What should a girl need to pack if she is going for ILP training at Trivandrum?",
  "response": "For an ILP (Intensive Learning Program) training in Trivandrum, a girl should consider packing the following items:\n\nClothing:\n1. Comfortable, modest clothing suitable for Kerala's climate\n2. Light, breathable fabrics\n3. Formal/semi-formal attire for training sessions\n4. Salwar kameez or similar professional wear\n5. Light sweater or jacket for air-conditioned rooms\n6. Comfortable walking shoes\n7. Casual/comfortable shoes\n\nPersonal Care:\n1. Toiletries\n2. Personal hygiene products\n3. Sunscreen\n4. Mosquito repellent\n5. First aid kit\n6. Necessary medications\n7. Hand sanitizer\n\nDocuments:\n1. Government ID\n2. Training program documents\n3. Travel documents\n4. Passport/Aadhar card\n5. Medical insurance card\n\nElectronics:\n1. Mobile phone\n2. Charger and power bank\n3. Laptop/tablet (if required)\n4. Universal adapter\n\nTraining Essentials:\n1. Notebook\n2. Pens/stationery\n3. Water bottle\n4. Small backpack/bag for daily use\n\nAdditional Recommendations:\n1. Light raincoat/umbrella\n2. Comfortable undergarments\n3. Face masks\n\nRemember to check specific training guidelines for any additional requirements.",
